OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FHoliday let tax changes to 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fgo ahead in Wales          
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The Welsh government has confirmed it  
OL,6, will go ahead with changes to council  
OL,7, tax that will make it harder for       
OL,8, holiday lets to be exempt.             
OL,10,FFrom next April they will need to be   
OL,11,Frented for 182 days in a year before   
OL,12,Fthey are allowed to pay business rates 
OL,13,Finstead.                               
OL,15,FIt comes as second home owners face a  
OL,16,F300% council tax premium.              
OL,18,FThe Welsh Conservatives said the move  
OL,19,Fwas a "devastating blow to             
OL,20,Fself-catering accommodation providers".
